						               													<description>The basic Marvel Scene It?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Comes in a 'cardboard' box' and not a tin like the deluxe version.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As with other Scene It? games, the object is to travel around the board and get to the end.  Finishing with an 'All Play To Win' before all others.  If that should fail, each round is a series of questions that get increasing easy as others get a chance to catch up.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Contents&amp;#10;DVD&amp;#10;Game Board&amp;#10;Six sided movement die number one to six&amp;#10;eight sided category die&amp;#10;4 metal player pieces&amp;#10;4 category reference cards&amp;#10;30 'Buzz' Cards&amp;#10;160 Trivia Cards&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game requires that you supply the TV and DVD Player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Categories:&amp;#10;My Play - current player gets a question from the DVD&amp;#10;All Play - All Players race to be the first to correctly answer question from DVD&amp;#10;Triple Threat - Answer a trivia question based on three clues&amp;#10;Screen Test - Answer a 'movie' trivia question&amp;#10;Power House - Answer a 'comic' trivia question&amp;#10;'buzz' - draw an 'action' card&amp;#10;Player's Choice - Choice one of the three trivia categories or My Play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Alternate rules for Longer Games, Shorter Games and 'Party Play'&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
